cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DS 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with weight pruning methods for deep neural networks. It may also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as DNNs are commonly used in computer vision tasks. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as DNNs are a popular tool in AI research. It may also be relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it deals with neural networks, and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as it involves optimization and iterative methods.
